PHASE 10 — HOMEPAGE REDESIGN (cinematic, scroll-driven) — DONE 2026-06-26

Landing page (/) rebuilt into a dark, lunarpunk, scroll-driven experience that
matches the player's palette (cyan→violet→magenta neon glow). The /app player
is untouched.

Centerpiece: a scroll-driven LAYOUT MORPH. A stylized CSS/SVG mock of the player
(not the heavy real player) pins to the viewport and morphs through the four
layout modes — split → slides-focus → video-focus → overlap/PiP — as you scroll,
each paired with a caption that lights up. Lenis (vendored locally, static) drives
smooth scroll; an rAF reader maps scroll progress → data-step; GPU transitions on
flex-grow keep it ~60fps.

Sections (IntersectionObserver reveals): hero (name + one-liner + "▶ Load a demo"),
scroll-morph showcase, any-source (YouTube/MP4/IPFS/WebTorrent), "your talk, kept
alive" persistence/roadmap teaser, open-source/self-host, final CTA, footer.

Demos: "▶ Load a demo" opens a lightweight picker backed by a DEMOS gallery array
(MoaV first; placeholder for more). Graceful href fallback to app/?p=moav-pdf.

Tech depth moved to a dedicated Docs hub at /docs/ (docs/docs/index.html) linking
SPEC / AUTHORING / JSON schema / Builder / Host / README / HOSTING / SERVICE /
ROADMAP. Nav "Docs" link added.

Accessibility/perf: prefers-reduced-motion → static fallback (no morph/ambience,
all revealed, pinned track released); <noscript> reveals content + collapses the
track; mobile uses a shorter pinned track and degrades gracefully; OG/meta updated;
Lenis vendored (~18KB) so the site stays static + offline-capable.

Files:
- docs/index.html         (redesigned landing page + noscript fallback + demo dialog)
- docs/home.css           (cinematic theme, aurora, morph, reveals, reduced-motion)
- docs/home.js            (Lenis init, scroll morph driver, reveals, demo picker)
- docs/vendor/lenis.min.js (Lenis 1.3.25, MIT, vendored)
- docs/docs/index.html    (Docs hub)
- scripts/smoke.mjs       (home + docs-hub smoke coverage)

Verify:
